('tulip', 'Tulip', 'No-code frontline operations platform for building manufacturing apps without code',
 E'Tulip is a cloud-based frontline operations platform that enables manufacturing teams to digitize their shop floor processes without custom software development. The platform provides a no-code app builder that machine operators, process engineers, and quality managers use to create guided work instructions, inspection checklists, and assembly verification workflows. Apps connect to machines, sensors, and barcode scanners via Tulip''s edge connectivity layer, bringing real-time equipment data into the operator interface without complex OT/IT integration projects.\n\nThe analytics layer aggregates data across every connected workstation and process step, giving operations managers visibility into cycle times, defect rates, and throughput in real time. When a process step deviates from the standard - a torque value outside spec, a scan sequence skipped, a component not verified - Tulip captures the event and routes it to the appropriate team for disposition. This closed-loop between operator guidance, process data, and corrective action is what distinguishes Tulip from static work instruction systems.\n\nTulip is used across automotive, medical device, electronics, and consumer goods manufacturing. The platform handles both high-mix low-volume assembly and high-volume repetitive production. Because operators build and modify apps themselves using Tulip''s visual editor, the time from process problem to deployed solution compresses from months to days. Pricing is enterprise and requires a demo with the sales team. Deployments typically start with a pilot line before expanding across the facility.',
 'https://tulip.co', 'https://tulip.co',
 'paid', false, 0, 4.5, 1240, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['manufacturing', 'industry-4-0', 'quality-inspection'],
 ARRAY['No-code app builder enables process engineers to deploy without IT dependency', 'Real-time machine and sensor connectivity via edge devices', 'Closed-loop defect capture and corrective action workflow out of the box', 'Flexible enough for both high-mix assembly and high-volume repetitive production'],
 ARRAY['Enterprise pricing with no self-serve tier - requires sales engagement', 'Edge device setup requires onsite installation and configuration time', 'Most powerful when connected to machines - value is lower for purely manual processes', 'Custom analytics dashboards require familiarity with the builder interface'],
 ARRAY['Digital work instructions and guided assembly for operator training and compliance', 'Real-time quality inspection and defect capture on the production line', 'Process performance analytics for continuous improvement and cycle time reduction'],
 NOW()),

('uptake', 'Uptake', 'Industrial AI platform for predictive maintenance and asset performance management',
 E'Uptake is an industrial AI platform that applies machine learning to sensor and operational data from heavy industrial assets - turbines, locomotives, mining equipment, and fleet vehicles - to predict failures before they happen and optimize maintenance scheduling. Rather than relying on time-based preventive maintenance schedules, Uptake models the actual health state of each asset by analyzing vibration, temperature, pressure, and operational signals continuously.\n\nThe predictive maintenance models flag anomalies that indicate an emerging failure hours or days before the event occurs, giving maintenance teams the window to schedule repairs during planned downtime rather than responding to costly unplanned breakdowns. For industries where a single equipment failure can shut down a production line or strand a vehicle in the field, the ROI comes directly from avoided downtime events. Uptake quantifies predicted failure risk, failure mode probability, and recommended action in a clear maintenance dashboard that technicians can act on without interpreting raw model outputs.\n\nUptake serves customers in energy, rail, construction, and mining. The platform integrates with CMMS systems like IBM Maximo and SAP PM to push work orders automatically when a predicted failure crosses a risk threshold. Asset health scoring provides fleet-level visibility for maintenance managers, while drill-down views surface the specific fault signals driving each prediction. Uptake is a Midwest-founded company with strong North American railroad and energy sector deployments. Pricing is enterprise and structured around asset count and data volume.',
 'https://uptake.com', 'https://uptake.com',
 'paid', false, 0, 4.3, 980, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['predictive-maintenance', 'industrial-ai', 'manufacturing'],
 ARRAY['Predicts failures hours to days in advance with specific failure mode diagnosis', 'Integrates with SAP PM and IBM Maximo to auto-generate work orders on threshold breach', 'Asset health scoring gives fleet-level maintenance visibility at a glance', 'Reduces unplanned downtime which drives direct, measurable ROI in heavy industry'],
 ARRAY['Enterprise only - no SMB or mid-market self-serve option', 'Requires 6-12 months of historical sensor data to train reliable predictive models', 'Implementation complexity is high for first asset class deployment', 'Coverage is strongest for North American rail and energy - less depth in other verticals'],
 ARRAY['Predictive failure detection for turbines, locomotives, and heavy equipment fleets', 'Condition-based maintenance scheduling to replace time-based service intervals', 'Fleet health dashboards for maintenance managers tracking asset availability and risk'],
 NOW()),

('augury', 'Augury', 'Machine health AI for continuous vibration monitoring and predictive maintenance',
 E'Augury is a machine health AI company that combines continuous vibration and ultrasound sensors with cloud-based machine learning to monitor rotating equipment health 24 hours a day. The hardware-plus-software platform attaches sensors to pumps, compressors, fans, and motors, then streams the signal data to Augury''s cloud platform where AI models detect bearing wear, imbalance, misalignment, and other mechanical fault signatures before they cause failures.\n\nAugury''s diagnostic AI classifies fault types with enough specificity that maintenance technicians receive an actionable recommendation - not just "anomaly detected" but "bearing inner race wear, replace within 14 days" with confidence scoring. The platform has been trained on over a trillion data points of machine behavior across thousands of global deployments, which gives its models a diagnostic accuracy that custom one-off implementations typically cannot match. Customers report a 10-to-1 return on investment from prevented failures, reduced parts costs, and extended asset life.\n\nThe platform is used in food and beverage, pharmaceutical, automotive, and consumer goods manufacturing. Augury''s People, Process and Technology framework pairs the software with human reliability engineers who help customers interpret results and build a reliability-centered maintenance culture. A dedicated mobile app gives technicians instant access to machine health alerts and diagnostic detail from the shop floor. The combination of always-on sensors, AI diagnostics, and human expert support has made Augury one of the most widely deployed machine health platforms globally. Pricing is based on the number of monitored machines and contract duration.',
 'https://augury.com', 'https://augury.com',
 'paid', false, 0, 4.6, 2100, false, true, false,
 ARRAY['predictive-maintenance', 'manufacturing', 'industrial-ai'],
 ARRAY['Always-on vibration and ultrasound monitoring catches faults missed in periodic inspections', 'AI diagnostics name specific fault types and recommend actions - not just anomaly scores', 'Trained on over a trillion data points across global deployments for high accuracy', 'Human reliability engineer support paired with the software platform'],
 ARRAY['Hardware sensor installation requires scheduled plant shutdown time per machine', 'Primarily covers rotating equipment - less applicable to process or static equipment', 'Full ROI realization takes 6-18 months as the model learns site-specific baselines', 'Enterprise pricing - not accessible for small plants with tight capital budgets'],
 ARRAY['Continuous health monitoring for pumps, compressors, fans, and motors in production facilities', 'Predictive maintenance program building to reduce unplanned downtime and emergency repair spend', 'Reliability-centered maintenance culture development for operations teams new to condition monitoring'],
 NOW()),

('sight-machine', 'Sight Machine', 'Manufacturing analytics platform for process optimization across complex production operations',
 E'Sight Machine is a manufacturing analytics platform that ingests data from machines, sensors, MES, ERP, and quality systems to create a unified digital model of a production operation. The platform normalizes data from disparate sources that were never designed to communicate, enabling engineers and operations managers to analyze production performance, identify root causes of quality variation, and model the impact of process changes before implementing them on the shop floor.\n\nThe analytics applications cover overall equipment effectiveness (OEE) tracking, quality analytics, yield optimization, and energy efficiency. Sight Machine''s AI models surface correlations between process parameters and output quality that are invisible in siloed data sources - for example, identifying that a specific combination of temperature, feed rate, and humidity predicts a yield loss event two shifts in advance. This prescriptive analytics capability moves manufacturing analytics beyond backward-looking dashboards to forward-looking process guidance.\n\nSight Machine serves process manufacturers in automotive, food and beverage, consumer goods, and semiconductor industries. The platform is cloud-hosted with edge components for real-time data capture in factories with limited connectivity. A digital factory model visualizes the entire production operation from raw material input to finished goods output, with performance metrics at every step. Sight Machine integrates with Siemens MindSphere, OSIsoft PI, and major ERP systems. Enterprise deployment with professional services engagement is standard. Pricing is custom and requires a discovery conversation with the sales team.',
 'https://sightmachine.com', 'https://sightmachine.com',
 'paid', false, 0, 4.2, 1050, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['manufacturing', 'industry-4-0', 'supply-chain'],
 ARRAY['Unified data model normalizes data from disparate machines, MES, ERP, and quality systems', 'Prescriptive analytics surfaces process-parameter correlations that predict yield and quality outcomes', 'Digital factory model visualizes end-to-end production performance in one view', 'Strong integration ecosystem covering Siemens MindSphere, OSIsoft PI, and major ERPs'],
 ARRAY['Complex implementation - data normalization across legacy systems requires significant professional services', 'Primarily serves large process manufacturers - not well suited to job shop or low-volume operations', 'Custom pricing with no published tiers makes it harder to budget without sales engagement', 'Full value requires data historians and MES already in place as data sources'],
 ARRAY['OEE tracking and root cause analysis across multi-line production facilities', 'Yield optimization through AI-identified correlations between process parameters and quality outcomes', 'Energy efficiency analysis to reduce utility costs per unit of production output'],
 NOW()),

('c3-ai', 'C3 AI', 'Enterprise AI platform for large-scale industrial and business AI application deployment',
 E'C3 AI is an enterprise AI software platform founded by Tom Siebel that enables large organizations to build and deploy AI applications across industrial and business operations. Unlike point solutions, C3 AI provides a platform layer that connects to existing enterprise data sources - historians, SCADA, ERP, CRM, supply chain systems - and applies pre-built and customizable AI models for use cases including predictive maintenance, inventory optimization, fraud detection, and demand forecasting.\n\nThe C3 AI suite includes application-specific products: C3 AI Reliability for predictive maintenance, C3 AI Inventory Optimization for supply chain, C3 AI CRM for enterprise customer intelligence, and C3 AI Ex Machina for no-code AI model building. The platform''s architecture handles the data integration, model training, and deployment infrastructure that makes enterprise AI projects expensive and slow in custom-built approaches, enabling faster time to value for large organizations with complex IT environments.\n\nC3 AI''s customer base includes major utilities, oil and gas companies, defense contractors, and industrial manufacturers. The platform is used at Baker Hughes for industrial AI across oilfield equipment, at the US Air Force for predictive maintenance on aircraft, and at several major utilities for grid reliability. In 2026, C3 AI''s integration with Microsoft Azure and AWS makes deployment in existing cloud environments more streamlined. The platform competes with Palantir and GE Vernova for large-scale industrial AI. Pricing is enterprise and contract-based with values typically in the seven-figure range annually for large deployments.',
 'https://c3.ai', 'https://c3.ai',
