('instrumental', 'Instrumental', 'AI-powered manufacturing quality platform for root cause analysis and yield improvement',
 E'Instrumental is an AI manufacturing quality platform that helps hardware product companies find and fix quality and yield problems faster by applying computer vision and machine learning to manufacturing process data. The platform captures images and measurements at inspection steps throughout the production line and uses AI to identify which process variations are causing defects and field failures before products ship to customers.\n\nThe core capability is root cause analysis: when a defect pattern emerges in production or a product returns from the field, Instrumental''s AI searches through captured manufacturing images and process data to identify which production step, operator, machine, or component variant correlates with the failure. Root cause investigations that previously took weeks of manual data analysis now complete in hours. For contract manufacturing environments where the brand owner lacks direct access to factory data, Instrumental provides a shared data layer between the OEM and the CM.\n\nInstrumental serves companies building complex hardware products - consumer electronics, medical devices, and automotive components - where a single yield improvement of 1% can represent millions of dollars in recovered product. The platform is deployed both at company-owned factories and at contract manufacturing partners. Integration with existing MES and test systems allows Instrumental to correlate quality outcomes with upstream process parameters that production data systems did not previously connect. Pricing is based on the number of production lines and contract duration; engagements typically start with a pilot on one product line before expanding.',
 'https://instrumental.com', 'https://instrumental.com',
 'paid', false, 0, 4.4, 890, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['quality-inspection', 'manufacturing', 'computer-vision'],
 ARRAY['AI root cause analysis compresses defect investigations from weeks to hours', 'Computer vision captures image evidence at every inspection step for retrospective analysis', 'Bridges data visibility gap between OEM brand owners and contract manufacturing partners', 'Field failure analysis connects customer returns back to specific manufacturing process deviations'],
 ARRAY['Hardware and sensors must be installed at each inspection station on the production line', 'Primarily suited to complex discrete manufacturing - less applicable to batch process industries', 'ROI is most compelling at high production volumes where yield gains are large in absolute units', 'Enterprise pricing with pilot-first sales motion lengthens the evaluation process'],
 ARRAY['Yield improvement root cause analysis for consumer electronics and medical device manufacturers', 'Contract manufacturing quality oversight enabling OEMs to monitor partner factory performance', 'Field failure investigation connecting returned products to manufacturing process deviations'],
 NOW()),

('cognex', 'Cognex', 'Machine vision systems and AI-powered inspection tools for factory automation',
 E'Cognex is the global leader in machine vision technology, providing industrial cameras, vision sensors, software, and AI-powered inspection systems used in automated production lines worldwide. Cognex vision systems identify, inspect, and guide manufactured parts at machine speed - verifying correct assembly, reading barcodes and 2D codes, measuring dimensional tolerances, and detecting surface defects across industries including automotive, electronics, consumer goods, and pharmaceuticals.\n\nIn 2026, Cognex''s AI capabilities are delivered through VisionPro Deep Learning and the In-Sight 2800 series - tools that apply deep learning to visual inspection tasks that traditional rule-based vision systems struggled with: inspecting irregular textures, detecting defects in patterned surfaces, and classifying complex assembly variations without writing explicit inspection rules. Plant engineers train the deep learning models using a GUI-based tool without requiring machine learning expertise, dramatically lowering the technical barrier to deploying AI inspection.\n\nCognex products are embedded in thousands of production facilities globally. The company operates as a hardware manufacturer and software platform vendor simultaneously - customers buy Cognex cameras and readers alongside the software that powers them. For discrete manufacturers automating inspection on high-speed production lines, Cognex is frequently the first-choice vendor for reliable, proven machine vision at production rates. The combination of hardware quality, software maturity, and deep integrations with major PLC and robot platforms makes Cognex the default choice for greenfield automation projects. Pricing varies significantly by product line - from standalone barcode readers at a few hundred dollars to full AI vision systems in the five- and six-figure range for complete line deployments.',
 'https://cognex.com', 'https://cognex.com',
 'paid', false, 0, 4.5, 3200, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['machine-vision', 'quality-inspection', 'manufacturing'],
 ARRAY['Global market leader in machine vision with proven reliability at production line speeds', 'Deep learning inspection tools trainable by plant engineers without ML expertise', 'Full stack - hardware cameras, software, and deep learning in one integrated platform', 'Broad integration support for major PLC brands, SCADA systems, and robot controllers'],
 ARRAY['Hardware costs are significant - full line deployments require substantial capital investment', 'System design and commissioning requires certified integrators for complex applications', 'Deep learning models require labeled training images which take time to collect and annotate', 'Less flexible than software-only vision platforms for rapidly changing product lines'],
