('elementary', 'Elementary', 'AI-powered visual inspection for SMB manufacturers replacing manual inspection stations',
 E'Elementary is a visual inspection AI company focused on bringing accessible, deployable quality control AI to small and mid-size manufacturers that lack the resources to implement enterprise-scale machine vision projects. The platform provides a software-first approach: customers mount standard industrial cameras at inspection stations, upload images of defective and conforming parts, and Elementary''s AI trains a custom inspection model within hours without requiring engineering services or specialist integration work.\n\nThe camera-agnostic approach is a deliberate design choice. Elementary works with cameras from major industrial suppliers that manufacturers likely already own or can purchase at standard market rates, eliminating the hardware vendor lock-in that characterizes enterprise machine vision systems. The deployment workflow is designed for a manufacturing quality engineer to execute independently - install cameras, collect training images, label defects using Elementary''s browser-based annotation tool, train the model, and deploy to the inspection station in a process that takes days, not months.\n\nElementary targets SMB manufacturers in metal fabrication, plastics, food processing, and general discrete manufacturing where manual inspection is the current standard and the cost to replace it with traditional machine vision systems has been prohibitive. The AI inspection models run locally on standard industrial PCs with GPU cards, keeping inspection latency under 200 milliseconds per part at typical production rates. In 2026, Elementary added a fleet management feature allowing quality engineers to manage models across multiple inspection stations from a single cloud dashboard. Pricing is subscription-based per deployment, with plans designed to be accessible to manufacturers at the SMB scale.',
 'https://elementary.ai', 'https://elementary.ai',
